EX ABUNDANTI.body:
Out of abundance;
abundantly; superfluously; more than sufficient. Calvin.

EX ABUNDANTI CAUTELA. Lat.
Out of abundant caution. "The practice
has arisen ex abundanti cautela." 8 East, 326;
Lord Ellenborough, 4 Maule & S. 544.
